The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 December is 9,238 (1,069.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 November, there were 545 new confirmed cases (63.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 November, there were 882 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 38% (337 fewer cases).
